==English==

===Noun===
'''metastability'''
# An unstable but potentially long-lived state of a chemical or physical system.
examples : [[supersaturated]] solution or an excited [[atom]]

===Adjective===
'''metastable'''
# The quality of being in an unstable but potentially long lived state.


'''Note''': This word is often (as in the wuote below) used in the context of an [[analogy]], and not in the literal, scientific meaning.

